name: Nezzar and Lucky Number
statement: Nezzar's favorite digit among $$$1,\ldots,9$$$ is $$$d$$$. He calls a positive integer lucky if $$$d$$$ occurs at least once in its decimal representation. Given $$$q$$$ integers $$$a_1,a_2,\ldots,a_q$$$, for each $$$1 \le i \le q$$$ Nezzar would like to know if $$$a_i$$$ can be equal to a sum of several (one or more) lucky numbers.
inputFormat: The first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 9$$$) â€” the number of test cases. The first line of each test case contains two integers $$$q$$$ and $$$d$$$ ($$$1 \le q \le 10^4$$$, $$$1 \le d \le 9$$$). The second line of each test case contains $$$q$$$ integers $$$a_1,a_2,\ldots,a_q$$$ ($$$1 \le a_i \le 10^9$$$).
outputFormat: For each integer in each test case, print " YES " in a single line if $$$a_i$$$ can be equal to a sum of lucky numbers. Otherwise, print " NO ". You can print letters in any case (upper or lower).
